25|$|Historically, {{standard}} Gatwick Express services did {{not charge}} <b>penalty</b> <b>fares</b> and permitted tickets to be purchased on board at no extra charge. Journeys {{to or from}} stations south of Gatwick were subject to <b>penalty</b> <b>fares</b> as normal. This rule applied to the six weekday services each way that start or end at Brighton.|$|R
